tourBios.exmtStatus: Conditional - Additional Qualifying Tournament Finisher or Finished 76-100 on 2015 Web.com Tour Money List
tourBios.carHigh:
2015: Played in 20 Web.com Tour events, making eight cuts. Best finish was a fifth place at the Colombia Championship in February on rounds of 66-68-68-69. Posted one more top 25 (T25) in July at the Nova Scotia Open. Finished the season 90th on the money list. 

2014: Finished the year by making 14 of 17 cuts on Latinoamérica and had six top-10 finishes, including his first career win...Ended the spring season with a solo fifth at the Lexus Panama Classic and moved to No. 18 on the Order of Merit...With limited conditional status, made three Web.com Tour starts in the summer, missing cuts at the Cleveland Open, Stonebrae Classic and Price Cutter Charity Championship. Was over par in each of the first rounds he played but under par in each of the second rounds...In late September, opened the fall season with a win at the Ecuador Open on Latinoamérica by five shots over four players. Collected $27,000 and moved from No. 18 to No. 4 on the Tour's Order of Merit...Two weeks later, won the TransAmerican Power Products CRV Mazatlan Open in Mexico in a one-hole playoff over Jorge Fernandez-Valdes on the same tour. Earned another $27,000 and jumped to No. 2 in Tour earnings. Followed up by making five of six cuts and had a pair of top-10 finishes to close out the year. His solo fourth at the season-ending Argentine Open left him No. 3 on the final Order of Merit...Played in three Web.com Tour events in the summer, missing the cut in all three.

2013: In his only career Web.com Tour start, missed the cut at the Mylan Classic...Was runner-up at his second stage qualifier in Brooksville, Fla. at the Web.com Tour Qualifying Tournament in November.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Two-time honorable-mention All-American at the University of Florida...Was a member of the 2008 state champion Nease High School golf team.
tourBios.personal: Says his biggest thrill in golf was beating high school arch nemesis in the Florida State Junior Amateur...Biggest thrill outside golf was surfing 15-foot waves in Puerto Rico...Lists the favorite golf courses as Pebble Beach and Timuquana CC in Jacksonville, Fla...Favorite college team is the Florida Gators and favorite professional team is the Jacksonville Jaguars...Would most like to be Mike Tyson for a day "to know what goes on in his head."..Would round out his dream foursome with Penelope Cruz, Angelina Jolie and Jennifer Aniston...Bucket list includes kissing Aniston and surfing the North Shore "without dying."...Favorite quote is "If you're not living on the edge, you're taking up too much room."..Twitter account name is @tylermccumber.
